83
00:11:42,668 --> 00:11:48,149
On one occasion the Blessed One was dwelling at Baranasi in the deer park at Isipatana.

84
00:11:48,932 --> 00:11:52,345
There the Blessed One addressed the monks of the group of five thus,

85
00:11:53,422 --> 00:11:57,730
Monks, these two extremes should not be followed by one who has gone forth into homelessness.

86
00:11:58,471 --> 00:12:00,274
What two?

87
00:12:00,293 --> 00:12:17,725
The pursuit of sensual happiness in sensual pleasures, which is low, vulgar, the way of worldlings, ignoble, unbeneficial, and the pursuit of self-mortification, which is painful, ignoble, unbeneficial.

88
00:12:17,822 --> 00:12:32,743
Without veering toward either of these extremes, the Tathagata has awakened to the middle way, which gives rise to vision, which gives rise to knowledge, and leads to peace, to direct knowledge, to enlightenment, to nibbana.

89
00:12:35,068 --> 00:12:39,600
And what, monks, is that middle way awakened to by the Tathagata?

90
00:12:40,283 --> 00:12:50,529
It is this noble eightfold path that is right view, right intention, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort,

91
00:12:50,509 --> 00:12:53,054
right mindfulness, right concentration.

92
00:12:53,916 --> 00:13:04,755
This, monks, is that middle way awakened to by the Tathagata, which gives rise to vision, which gives rise to knowledge, and leads to peace, to direct knowledge, to enlightenment, to nibbana.

93
00:13:06,057 --> 00:13:08,602
Now this, monks, is the noble truth of suffering,

94
00:13:09,038 --> 00:13:22,389
Birth is suffering, aging is suffering, illness is suffering, death is suffering, union with what is displeasing is suffering, separation from what is pleasing is suffering, not to get what one wants is suffering.

95
00:13:22,811 --> 00:13:26,440
In brief, the five aggregates subject to clinging are suffering.

96
00:13:27,230 --> 00:13:31,975
Now this monks is the noble truth of the origin of suffering.

97
00:13:32,856 --> 00:13:39,546
It is this craving that leads to renewed existence, accompanied by delight and lust, seeking delight here and there.

98
00:13:40,246 --> 00:13:45,352
That is craving for sensual pleasures, craving for existence, craving for extermination.

99
00:13:46,534 --> 00:13:49,879
Now this monks is the noble truth of the cessation of suffering.

100
00:13:50,347 --> 00:13:59,399
It is the remainderless fading away and cessation of that same craving, the giving up and relinquishing of it, freedom from it, non-attachment.

101
00:13:59,419 --> 00:14:04,105
Now this, monks, is the noble truth of the way leading to the cessation of suffering.

102
00:14:04,966 --> 00:14:09,133
It is this noble eightfold path that is right view,

103
00:14:12,826 --> 00:14:21,975
Right view, right intention, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness.

104
00:14:25,178 --> 00:14:26,240
Right concentration.

105
00:14:29,322 --> 00:14:30,884
Sadhu.

106
